# air_quality_api/
# ├── datahandler.py         # Data model logic (Air Quality Calculations)
# ├── api.py                 # Flask server (Backend API)
# ├── requirements.txt       # Flask dependencies (Flask, pandas, etc.)

# air_quality_dashboard/
# ├── dashboard_app.py       # Streamlit frontend (Client)
# ├── requirements.txt       # Streamlit dependencies (streamlit, pandas, plotly)



# pip install -r air_quality_api/requirements.txt
# pip install -r air_quality_dashboard/requirements.txt

# ---

# ## Step 1: Start the Flask Backend (The API)

# The Flask API handles the data processing and sits on **port 5000**. Streamlit will talk to this port.

# 1.  **Open your command prompt/terminal.**
# 2.  **Navigate to the Flask directory:**
#     ```bash
#     cd air_quality_api
#     3.  **Run the API server:**
#     ```bash
#     python api.py
    
# **Keep this terminal window open.** It should show output confirming the server is running on `http://127.0.0.1:5000`. If you see any errors here (like `FileNotFoundError`), you must fix them before moving to Step 2.

# ---

# ## Step 2: Start the Streamlit Frontend (The Dashboard)

# The Streamlit app is the web interface that requests data from the running Flask API.

# 1.  **Open a SECOND command prompt/terminal window.**
# 2.  **Navigate to the Streamlit directory:**
#     ```bash
#     cd air_quality_dashboard
#     3.  **Run the Streamlit application:**
#     ```bash
#     streamlit run dashboard_app.py
    
# Streamlit will automatically open a new browser tab (usually at `http://localhost:8501`). The dashboard will then attempt to fetch data from the Flask server you started in Step 1.

# ---

# ## Summary of Execution

# You must have **two terminal windows running simultaneously**:

# | Terminal Window | Folder | Command | Purpose |
# | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
# | **1 (Backend)** | `air_quality_api` | `python api.py` | **Runs your model/data handler.** |
# | **2 (Frontend)** | `air_quality_dashboard` | `streamlit run dashboard_app.py` | **Runs the web interface.** |




